research_municipality_step.notes: Forest Hill, TX operates under a Council-Manager form of government, with a Mayor and six City Council members. The 'mayor_council' government type was selected as the closest match from the provided options. The elected officials and their roles were identified from the city's official website and related search results. Council members are elected at large for three-year terms. Some council members have designated 'Place' numbers, which are included as divisions where explicitly stated in the search results.
